  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Social sourcing: uplifting the living conditions in the Sundays River Valley communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In this project, Total Produce B.V. (importer) and SRCC (supplier) aim to strengthen inclusion and improve living conditions of farm- and factory workers, through  (1) improved transparency, (2) representation of workers and their communities, (3) funding of basic services and economic opportunities in local communities and (4) awareness of economic opportunities throughout the value chain. Total Produce B.V. and SRCC will explore a new sourcing approach, in which not only a commercial relationship between supplier and importer takes a prominent role, but also the social and human value of the trade. The long-term goal of this new sourcing strategy is to support disclosure and collective action to address social and environmental issues that are impacted by business.</narrative>
  </description>
